// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § Audit-axis tagging  (per-event audit-row schema)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// Emit-side audit-row tag. Used by the audit-port to discriminate.
const AUDIT_TAG_OBSERVE     : &str = "chat-sync.observe" ;
const AUDIT_TAG_TICK_EMIT   : &str = "chat-sync.tick.emit" ;
const AUDIT_TAG_TICK_DROP   : &str = "chat-sync.tick.drop-cap-denied" ;
const AUDIT_TAG_INGEST_OK   : &str = "chat-sync.ingest.ok" ;
const AUDIT_TAG_INGEST_DENY : &str = "chat-sync.ingest.cap-denied" ;
const AUDIT_TAG_REVOKE      : &str = "chat-sync.revoke" ;
const AUDIT_TAG_PURGE_RECV  : &str = "chat-sync.purge.received" ;

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § Sovereign-revoke flow  (break-glass · ¬ surveillance · "right to be forgotten")
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// User-flow steps :
//   1. User invokes break-glass UI (Ctrl+Shift+Alt+S in Mycelium Desktop).
//   2. Host calls `__cssl_mycelium_chat_revoke(my_handle, now_unix)`.
//   3. Service zeros the cap-policy for `my_handle`        (step 1 of 5).
//   4. Service purges local ChatPatternRing                (step 2 of 5).
//   5. Service purges local federation-emitter-record      (step 3 of 5).
//   6. Service broadcasts PurgeRequest{handle, ts_unix}    (step 4 of 5).
//   7. Each peer that receives the PurgeRequest applies it locally :
//        a. peer-side `__cssl_mycelium_chat_handle_purge` drops the
//           emitter from EVERY public-set bucket
//        b. patterns whose distinct-emitter-count drops below k_floor
//           transition staged ; no longer visible to GM/DM modulation
//   8. Service bumps revoke-stat counter                   (step 5 of 5).
//
// After revoke, the emitter contributes ZERO to any aggregated-shape from
// this point forward. The audit-row at step 1 is the immutable record of
// the revoke event ; the broadcast at step 6 is best-effort (peers may be
// offline at revoke-time ; they apply the purge on next-poll-cycle).
//
// IDEMPOTENCY : repeated revoke calls are no-ops after the first ; safe to
// retry across crash-recovery + replay.

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § Compliance attestation
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// Σ-mask gates appear at TWO points :
//   - emit-side  : MyceliumChatSync::tick (host-side · `cap_flags & CAP_EMIT_ALLOWED`)
//   - ingest-side : ChatPatternFederation::ingest (host-side · `cap_flags & CAP_FEDERATION_INGEST`)
//
// k-anonymity floor enforced @ ChatPatternFederation::snapshot_public ;
// patterns below k_floor never reach `out_shape` in `lookup_shape`.
//
// Determinism : `federation_blake3` is replay-stable per-snapshot. A GM/DM
// persona seeded with `(persona_seed, federation_blake3)` yields identical
// modulation across replays.
//
// ¬ raw-chat-text egress : ChatPattern is a 32-byte fixed-shape blob.
// pattern_id is content-addressable over (intent · response · phase) ;
// emitter_handle is a non-recoverable BLAKE3-trunc of pubkey.
//
// Attestation : there was no hurt nor harm in the making of this.
